If guys who had
dandruff, if guys

00:23:56.950 --> 00:23:58.890 align:middle line:84%
who itched at
inappropriate times,

00:23:58.890 --> 00:24:01.190 align:middle line:84%
if guys who made strange
noises in the bathroom,

00:24:01.190 --> 00:24:03.510 align:middle line:84%
if these people
could make history,

00:24:03.510 --> 00:24:05.800 align:middle line:84%
then it's your job and
my job to make history.

00:24:05.800 --> 00:24:07.970 align:middle line:84%
And Buzz, sometimes
you've had this,

00:24:07.970 --> 00:24:09.970 align:middle line:84%
because you perform in
front of live audiences

00:24:09.970 --> 00:24:10.680 align:middle line:90%
every one once in a while.

00:24:10.680 --> 00:24:12.890 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes when you're
performing for an audience,

00:24:12.890 --> 00:24:16.730 align:middle line:84%
their pupils dilate, they open
wide, and their face melts.

00:24:16.730 --> 00:24:17.540 align:middle line:90%
And it's--

00:24:17.540 --> 00:24:18.130 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They're mesmerized.

00:24:18.130 --> 00:24:20.046 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: Yeah, it's an
astonishing experience.

00:24:20.046 --> 00:24:21.210 align:middle line:90%
Buzz was like that.

00:24:21.210 --> 00:24:22.460 align:middle line:90%
And I couldn't understand why.

00:24:22.460 --> 00:24:24.470 align:middle line:84%
I noticed for the
first time after years

00:24:24.470 --> 00:24:26.252 align:middle line:84%
of knowing him that
his eyes were blue.

00:24:26.252 --> 00:24:28.710 align:middle line:84%
I noticed for the first that
he was even shorter than I am,

00:24:28.710 --> 00:24:29.882 align:middle line:90%
which is hard, really hard.

00:24:29.882 --> 00:24:32.090 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's good for
stuffing him into a tin can--

00:24:32.090 --> 00:24:33.050 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, yeah. it worked.

00:24:33.050 --> 00:24:33.960 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: --and sending
him into space, yeah.

00:24:33.960 --> 00:24:34.876 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's right.

00:24:34.876 --> 00:24:37.230 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: So when I was
finished, I was so embarrassed,

00:24:37.230 --> 00:24:38.140 align:middle line:90%
it was ridiculous.

00:24:38.140 --> 00:24:39.639 align:middle line:84%
And basically, I
was telling myself,

00:24:39.639 --> 00:24:42.080 align:middle line:84%
Bloom, you idiot, don't
you realize this guy's

00:24:42.080 --> 00:24:44.210 align:middle line:84%
been in history
books for 40 years?

00:24:44.210 --> 00:24:46.590 align:middle line:84%
For three months I kicked
myself around the block

00:24:46.590 --> 00:24:48.930 align:middle line:84%
for having embarrassed
myself in this way.

00:24:48.930 --> 00:24:50.430 align:middle line:90%
And then I realized something.

00:24:50.430 --> 00:24:52.800 align:middle line:84%
Buzz did the highest thing
that he could possibly

00:24:52.800 --> 00:24:54.440 align:middle line:84%
ever do-- setting
foot on the Moon.

00:24:54.440 --> 00:24:57.270 align:middle line:84%
He was the spear tip of
a $120 billion project--

00:24:57.270 --> 00:24:59.400 align:middle line:84%
so once-in-a-lifetime
experience.

00:24:59.400 --> 00:25:01.230 align:middle line:84%
When he came back
from the Moon, he

00:25:01.230 --> 00:25:06.420 align:middle line:84%
went into a state of alcoholism
and depression for 10 years.

00:25:06.420 --> 00:25:11.300 align:middle line:84%
It was very, very hard for him
to find new purposes in life.

00:25:11.300 --> 00:25:12.540 align:middle line:90%
And we all need purpose.

00:25:12.540 --> 00:25:13.800 align:middle line:90%
It's back to that business--

00:25:13.800 --> 00:25:13.990 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It was a letdown.

00:25:13.990 --> 00:25:16.070 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: --the
transcendent truth, yeah.

00:25:16.070 --> 00:25:18.750 align:middle line:84%
He needed that lecture
probably more than anybody else

00:25:18.750 --> 00:25:21.600 align:middle line:84%
I've ever been
inspired to give it to.

00:25:21.600 --> 00:25:24.360 align:middle line:84%
But what a weird thing
for your brain, you know,

00:25:24.360 --> 00:25:27.740 align:middle line:84%
when you consider yourself to be
reasonably intelligent to take

00:25:27.740 --> 00:25:30.450 align:middle line:84%
three months to figure out what,
apparently, your gut already

00:25:30.450 --> 00:25:31.500 align:middle line:90%
knew.

00:25:31.500 --> 00:25:32.874 align:middle line:90%
Very bizarre experience, George.

00:25:32.874 --> 00:25:34.790 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What are these
trinkets all over you?

00:25:34.790 --> 00:25:36.748 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: These are the
expansions of my powers,

00:25:36.748 --> 00:25:37.850 align:middle line:90%
thanks to technology.

00:25:37.850 --> 00:25:41.350 align:middle line:84%
These are our prosthesis,
for all practical purposes.

00:25:41.350 --> 00:25:44.510 align:middle line:84%
These two things are
eight-hour recorders.

00:25:44.510 --> 00:25:48.980 align:middle line:84%
Back in when I was still
stuck in bed in 2000, 2001,

00:25:48.980 --> 00:25:51.390 align:middle line:84%
there was a very high-placed
advertising executive.

00:25:51.390 --> 00:25:55.780 align:middle line:84%
She did the branding for Reebok
and Nike, and PlayStation 2,

00:25:55.780 --> 00:25:57.030 align:middle line:90%
and all kinds of things.

00:25:57.030 --> 00:25:58.600 align:middle line:84%
And she used to come out
to the apartment once

00:25:58.600 --> 00:25:59.391 align:middle line:90%
every three months.

00:25:59.391 --> 00:26:01.060 align:middle line:90%
She was a huge fan of my books.

00:26:01.060 --> 00:26:03.100 align:middle line:84%
And she said, you
know, your real art

00:26:03.100 --> 00:26:04.374 align:middle line:90%
is verbal improvisation.

00:26:04.374 --> 00:26:06.540 align:middle line:84%
You have to start recording
everything that you say.

00:26:06.540 --> 00:26:09.360 align:middle line:84%
Now, I know that sounds
ridiculously egotistical,

00:26:09.360 --> 00:26:10.510 align:middle line:90%
but I followed her advice.

00:26:10.510 --> 00:26:12.610 align:middle line:84%
So these are eight-hour
recording devices.

00:26:12.610 --> 00:26:14.150 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you're constantly
recording yourself?

00:26:14.150 --> 00:26:14.790 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Everything.

00:26:14.790 --> 00:26:16.750 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, nobody ever will have
a chance to listen to it.

00:26:16.750 --> 00:26:18.125 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You mean,
what you and I

00:26:18.125 --> 00:26:20.588 align:middle line:84%
were talking about before
the show is on that thing?

00:26:20.588 --> 00:26:21.669 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:26:21.669 --> 00:26:24.210 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: Oh, those weird sexual
experiences of yours, George.

00:26:24.210 --> 00:26:25.470 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, thanks a lot.

00:26:25.470 --> 00:26:27.261 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: I promise
never to tell your wife.

00:26:27.261 --> 00:26:29.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is there a
12-minute gap there?

00:26:29.320 --> 00:26:33.420 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: No, one goes on
before the other one turns off.

00:26:33.420 --> 00:26:35.010 align:middle line:90%
So there's no 20-minute gaps.

00:26:35.010 --> 00:26:37.085 align:middle line:84%
But this is a
pedometer, so that I

00:26:37.085 --> 00:26:39.080 align:middle line:84%
can measure how far I'm
walking during the day.

00:26:39.080 --> 00:26:41.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, because you were
bedridden for how many years?

00:26:41.130 --> 00:26:42.671 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: I was
bedridden for 15 years

00:26:42.671 --> 00:26:44.557 align:middle line:84%
and for five years
was too weak to speak

00:26:44.557 --> 00:26:46.140 align:middle line:84%
a single word of the
English language.

00:26:46.140 --> 00:26:49.030 align:middle line:84%
>>You must just get excited
when you see I did a mile today.

00:26:49.030 --> 00:26:50.000 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Yes, exactly.

00:26:50.000 --> 00:26:51.500 align:middle line:84%
And these are two
Kindles, you know,

00:26:51.500 --> 00:26:53.600 align:middle line:84%
the Kindles read
out loud to me, so.

00:26:53.600 --> 00:26:55.602 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you go
through TSA security--

00:26:55.602 --> 00:26:56.185 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Yeah?

00:26:56.185 --> 00:26:57.950 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --do you have to
take all that stuff off?

00:26:57.950 --> 00:27:00.408 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: Yes, it takes about
20 minutes to take it all off.

00:27:00.408 --> 00:27:02.660 align:middle line:84%
It takes about 20 minutes
to put it all back on again.

00:27:02.660 --> 00:27:04.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I would not want
to be the guy behind you.

00:27:04.890 --> 00:27:06.660 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: No, I let
them go through.

00:27:06.660 --> 00:27:08.820 align:middle line:90%
I just make them go through.

00:27:08.820 --> 00:27:10.490 align:middle line:84%
But this stuff is
wonderful, George.

00:27:10.490 --> 00:27:12.860 align:middle line:84%
Just think, 20 years
ago, 30 years ago,

00:27:12.860 --> 00:27:15.185 align:middle line:84%
before the Walkman, so
that's about 40 years ago,

00:27:15.185 --> 00:27:16.810 align:middle line:84%
you and I used to
walk down the street,

00:27:16.810 --> 00:27:18.160 align:middle line:84%
and we were all by
ourselves, stuck

00:27:18.160 --> 00:27:19.140 align:middle line:90%
in the loneliness of our skulls.

00:27:19.140 --> 00:27:19.950 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: We didn't have phones.

00:27:19.950 --> 00:27:21.030 align:middle line:90%
We didn't have anything.

00:27:21.030 --> 00:27:21.140 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: That's right.

00:27:21.140 --> 00:27:22.265 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sometimes though--

00:27:22.265 --> 00:27:23.040 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Yeah?

00:27:23.040 --> 00:27:25.489 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --it was a
little more peaceful.

00:27:25.489 --> 00:27:28.030 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: But peace is not what
it's cracked up to be, George.

00:27:28.030 --> 00:27:29.890 align:middle line:84%
Excitement is what
it's cracked up to be.

00:27:29.890 --> 00:27:31.105 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So you like
this new technology?

00:27:31.105 --> 00:27:32.890 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: Oh, I love
having information

00:27:32.890 --> 00:27:34.960 align:middle line:84%
pouring through
me 24 hours a day.

00:27:34.960 --> 00:27:37.220 align:middle line:84%
You know, because I
was flying out here,

00:27:37.220 --> 00:27:39.762 align:middle line:84%
I was away from my information
for roughly an hour.

00:27:39.762 --> 00:27:40.720 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Did you freak?

00:27:40.720 --> 00:27:41.770 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: Yes.

00:27:41.770 --> 00:27:44.090 align:middle line:84%
I mean things are
happening in rock.

00:27:44.090 --> 00:27:45.537 align:middle line:90%
I need to be on those things.

00:27:45.537 --> 00:27:46.370 align:middle line:90%
All kinds of things.

00:27:46.370 --> 00:27:46.900 align:middle line:90%
I need to be on them--

00:27:46.900 --> 00:27:47.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: That's why I call
you the human computer.

00:27:47.880 --> 00:27:49.046 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: --minute by minute.

00:27:49.046 --> 00:27:50.870 align:middle line:84%
Right, that's why--
OK, nobody knows this,

00:27:50.870 --> 00:27:52.740 align:middle line:84%
but we've got to tell
the audience this.

00:27:52.740 --> 00:27:56.790 align:middle line:84%
So George's producer
calls me, sometimes

00:27:56.790 --> 00:27:58.550 align:middle line:90%
on 20-minutes' notice.

00:27:58.550 --> 00:28:01.975 align:middle line:84%
And in the old days, your
producer used to say,

00:28:01.975 --> 00:28:04.610 align:middle line:84%
do you know anything about
the following subject?

00:28:04.610 --> 00:28:06.120 align:middle line:84%
And of course, I
always answer yes,

00:28:06.120 --> 00:28:08.453 align:middle line:84%
because I'm not going to miss
going on the air with you.

00:28:08.453 --> 00:28:10.560 align:middle line:84%
What does she think
I am, an idiot?

00:28:10.560 --> 00:28:14.240 align:middle line:84%
So and then one night, it was
22 degrees in New York City.

00:28:14.240 --> 00:28:16.210 align:middle line:84%
I was stepping out
of the Tea Lounge,

00:28:16.210 --> 00:28:18.880 align:middle line:84%
this huge club where I've
written three books now.

00:28:18.880 --> 00:28:20.940 align:middle line:84%
I was about to go for my
walk through the park.

00:28:20.940 --> 00:28:23.270 align:middle line:84%
And my way home, last
thing I wanted to do

00:28:23.270 --> 00:28:24.539 align:middle line:90%
was take off my gloves.

00:28:24.539 --> 00:28:25.580 align:middle line:90%
The weather was horrible.

00:28:25.580 --> 00:28:25.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Sure.

00:28:25.960 --> 00:28:27.210 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: And the phone rang.

00:28:27.210 --> 00:28:28.500 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
should I take it--

00:28:28.500 --> 00:28:28.880 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you had to
take your gloves off.

00:28:28.880 --> 00:28:29.570 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: --should I take it?

00:28:29.570 --> 00:28:31.911 align:middle line:84%
So I took the gloves off
and I answered the phone.

00:28:31.911 --> 00:28:33.785 align:middle line:84%
And it was Lisa Lions,
one of your producers.

00:28:33.785 --> 00:28:35.940 align:middle line:84%
And Lisa said, do
you know anything

00:28:35.940 --> 00:28:37.284 align:middle line:90%
about the movie "Avatar"?

00:28:37.284 --> 00:28:39.450 align:middle line:84%
And I said, Lisa, I don't
have time to watch movies.

00:28:39.450 --> 00:28:40.790 align:middle line:90%
I don't know anything about it.

00:28:40.790 --> 00:28:43.060 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well, kids
are getting suicidal

00:28:43.060 --> 00:28:44.110 align:middle line:90%
after watching the film.

00:28:44.110 --> 00:28:44.776 align:middle line:90%
Do you know why?

00:28:44.776 --> 00:28:46.490 align:middle line:84%
And I said, yes, of
course, I know why.

00:28:46.490 --> 00:28:49.860 align:middle line:84%
And I told her about
Anousheh Ansari's depression

00:28:49.860 --> 00:28:51.830 align:middle line:84%
after she went up on
the International Space

00:28:51.830 --> 00:28:54.770 align:middle line:84%
Station for roughly 10 days
and came back to Earth.

00:28:54.770 --> 00:28:56.230 align:middle line:84%
And up there,
there'd been peace.

00:28:56.230 --> 00:28:57.390 align:middle line:90%
And she could hold the world--

00:28:57.390 --> 00:28:57.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Tranquility.

00:28:57.930 --> 00:28:59.440 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: --in the
palm of her hand.

00:28:59.440 --> 00:29:01.290 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
now, she was going back

00:29:01.290 --> 00:29:04.550 align:middle line:84%
to violence and hatred, and
road rage, and all these things.

00:29:04.550 --> 00:29:06.709 align:middle line:84%
And Lisa said, OK, can
you be on in 20 minutes?

00:29:06.709 --> 00:29:07.500 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You're on.

00:29:07.500 --> 00:29:10.880 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: So I am usually on
with you after two hours.

00:29:10.880 --> 00:29:12.790 align:middle line:84%
Now, I do my
homework like crazy,

00:29:12.790 --> 00:29:15.530 align:middle line:84%
because I want to give you
absolutely the best and most

00:29:15.530 --> 00:29:16.330 align:middle line:90%
recent facts I can.

00:29:16.330 --> 00:29:17.454 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: And you always do.

00:29:17.454 --> 00:29:19.310 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: But it's hard,
George, because you

00:29:19.310 --> 00:29:23.372 align:middle line:84%
are a former news-- whatever
the news guy is called.

00:29:23.372 --> 00:29:24.830 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, I
was the executive.

00:29:24.830 --> 00:29:27.530 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: Yeah, and so
you're so on top of the news

00:29:27.530 --> 00:29:28.950 align:middle line:90%
that it's ridiculous.

00:29:28.950 --> 00:29:31.547 align:middle line:84%
Two nights ago or three
nights ago when we did Iraq,

00:29:31.547 --> 00:29:33.130 align:middle line:84%
you already had half
the things that I

00:29:33.130 --> 00:29:34.922 align:middle line:84%
was going to tell you
right in your report.

00:29:34.922 --> 00:29:36.046 align:middle line:90%
And you're always that way.

00:29:36.046 --> 00:29:38.600 align:middle line:84%
You always have facts that
are so right up to the minute,

00:29:38.600 --> 00:29:39.060 align:middle line:90%
it's ridiculous.

00:29:39.060 --> 00:29:40.393 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Well, that's what I do.

00:29:40.393 --> 00:29:42.090 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: So running
the race with you

00:29:42.090 --> 00:29:44.520 align:middle line:84%
and keeping up with
you-- very hard.

00:29:44.520 --> 00:29:45.930 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: This has been fun.

00:29:45.930 --> 00:29:47.450 align:middle line:84%
In our next "Beyond
Belief," I want

00:29:47.450 --> 00:29:50.217 align:middle line:84%
to get into a segment
called "Ask Howard."

00:29:50.217 --> 00:29:52.050 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to do
some things like that.

00:29:52.050 --> 00:29:52.942 align:middle line:90%
But what drives you?

00:29:52.942 --> 00:29:53.900 align:middle line:90%
What keeps pushing you?

00:29:53.900 --> 00:29:55.860 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: I love
knowing things, and I

00:29:55.860 --> 00:29:58.260 align:middle line:84%
love being a value to
my fellow human beings.

00:29:58.260 --> 00:29:59.825 align:middle line:84%
So I love taking
all this information

00:29:59.825 --> 00:30:01.850 align:middle line:84%
and pouring it through
the sieve, the leaky

00:30:01.850 --> 00:30:02.800 align:middle line:90%
sieve of a brain.

00:30:02.800 --> 00:30:04.540 align:middle line:90%
It really is a leaky sieve.

00:30:04.540 --> 00:30:07.810 align:middle line:84%
And trying to see things
from points of view--

00:30:07.810 --> 00:30:09.307 align:middle line:84%
it's that second
law of science--

00:30:09.307 --> 00:30:11.140 align:middle line:84%
see things from points
of view they've never

00:30:11.140 --> 00:30:14.200 align:middle line:84%
been seen from before, so
that you don't get blindsided.

00:30:14.200 --> 00:30:16.580 align:middle line:10%
And if I can successfully
do that for you

00:30:16.580 --> 00:30:19.500 align:middle line:10%
or for the people at the Office
of the Secretary of Defense,

00:30:19.500 --> 00:30:23.000 align:middle line:10%
because they pulled
me in, or any other,

00:30:23.000 --> 00:30:26.540 align:middle line:10%
or the press for the 11th
president of India, who also

00:30:26.540 --> 00:30:28.990 align:middle line:10%
thinks I'm some
sort of something,

00:30:28.990 --> 00:30:33.380 align:middle line:10%
and Buzz Aldrin, hey, I'm having
a good day, I'm having a ball.

00:30:33.380 --> 00:30:36.044 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well, you give
off a lot of energy.

00:30:36.044 --> 00:30:37.460 align:middle line:84%
>>BLOOM: But--
it's because you're

00:30:37.460 --> 00:30:38.780 align:middle line:90%
giving me a lot of energy.

00:30:38.780 --> 00:30:41.030 align:middle line:84%
We get our energy
from the people

00:30:41.030 --> 00:30:44.410 align:middle line:84%
who are kind enough to
listen to us and energize us.

00:30:44.410 --> 00:30:47.234 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, this stuff is so much
fun, George, it's ridiculous.

00:30:47.234 --> 00:30:48.150 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: More to come.

00:30:48.150 --> 00:30:49.530 align:middle line:84%
Howard, thanks for being
on "Beyond Belief."

00:30:49.530 --> 00:30:50.380 align:middle line:90%
>>BLOOM: George, thank you.

00:30:50.380 --> 00:30:51.720 align:middle line:90%
